1. "I'm not a teacher: only a fellow traveler of whom you asked the way. I pointed ahead- ahead of myself as well as you." - George Bernard Shaw 
2. "The whole art of teaching is only the art of awakening the natural curiosity of young minds for the purpose of satisfying it afterwards." - Anatole France 
3. "Those who educate children well are more to be honoured than they who produce them; for these only gave them life, those the art of living well." - Aristotle 
4. "The art of teaching is the art of assisting discovery." - Mark Van Doren 
5. “The mediocre teacher tells. The good teacher explains.
6. "They inspire you, they entertain you, and you end up learning a ton even when you don't know it." - Nicholas Sparks 
7. "Let us remember: One book, one pen, one child, and one teacher can change the world." - Malala Yousafzai 
8. "A good teacher, like a good entertainer first must hold his audience's attention, then he can teach his lesson." - John Henrik Clarke 
9. “The mediocre teacher tells. The good teacher explains. The superior teacher demonstrates. The great teacher inspires.” ― William Arthur Ward 
11. “A teacher who loves learning earns the right and the ability to help others learn.” ― Ruth Beechick 
12. "One good teacher in a lifetime may sometimes change a delinquent into a solid citizen." - Philip Wylie 
13. “Teachers, I believe, are the most responsible and important members of society because their professional efforts affect the fate of the earth.” ― Helen Caldicott 
14. “Teachers can change lives with just the right mix of chalk and challenges.” ― Joyce Meyer 
